issues.description: The UML in the problem statement specifies addGuestStudents(int): void, but the reference solution implements addGuestStudents(int) returning boolean. Students following the UML will declare a void method, leading to signature mismatches when comparing to the solution or when writing tests.
issues.suggested_fix: Align the return type of addGuestStudents with the UML: either change the reference implementation to return void (removing the boolean result) or update the UML and problem text to reflect a boolean return type if that behavior is intended.
